{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":960,"text":"I'm here to tell you\nabout the real search for alien life."},{"time":4675,"text":"Not little green humanoids\narriving in shiny UFOs,"},{"time":7930,"text":"although that would be nice."},{"time":9678,"text":"But it's the search for planets\norbiting stars far away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13924,"text":"Every star in our sky is a sun."},{"time":15783,"text":"And if our sun has planets --"},{"time":17188,"text":"Mercury, Venus, Earth, Mars, etc.,"},{"time":19709,"text":"surely those other stars\nshould have planets also,"},{"time":22169,"text":"and they do."},{"time":23455,"text":"And in the last two decades,"},{"time":24891,"text":"astronomers have found\nthousands of exoplanets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28502,"text":"Our night sky is literally\nteeming with exoplanets."},{"time":31337,"text":"We know, statistically speaking,"},{"time":32913,"text":"that every star has at least one planet."},{"time":35984,"text":"And in the search for planets,"},{"time":37985,"text":"and in the future,\nplanets that might be like Earth,"},{"time":40775,"text":"we're able to help address"},{"time":42168,"text":"some of the most amazing\nand mysterious questions"},{"time":45041,"text":"that have faced humankind for centuries."},{"time":47636,"text":"Why are we here?"},{"time":49215,"text":"Why does our universe exist?"},{"time":51476,"text":"How did Earth form and evolve?"},{"time":53912,"text":"How and why did life originate\nand populate our planet?"},{"time":57665,"text":"The second question\nthat we often think about is:"},{"time":60744,"text":"Are we alone?"},{"time":62911,"text":"Is there life out there?"},{"time":65109,"text":"Who is out there?"},{"time":67783,"text":"You know, this question has been around\nfor thousands of years,"},{"time":70813,"text":"since at least the time\nof the Greek philosophers."},{"time":73254,"text":"But I'm here to tell you\njust how close we're getting"},{"time":75825,"text":"to finding out the answer\nto this question."},{"time":78730,"text":"It's the first time in human history\nthat this really is within reach for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83294,"text":"Now when I think about the possibilities\nfor life out there,"},{"time":86297,"text":"I think of the fact that our sun\nis but one of many stars."},{"time":90825,"text":"This is a photograph of a real galaxy,"},{"time":92727,"text":"we think our Milky Way\nlooks like this galaxy."},{"time":95197,"text":"It's a collection of bound stars."},{"time":96860,"text":"But our [sun] is one\nof hundreds of billions of stars"},{"time":101271,"text":"and our galaxy is one of upwards\nof hundreds of billions of galaxies."},{"time":106707,"text":"Knowing that small planets\nare very common,"},{"time":109498,"text":"you can just do the math."},{"time":111424,"text":"And there are just so many stars\nand so many planets out there,"},{"time":115449,"text":"that surely, there must be life\nsomewhere out there."},{"time":119060,"text":"Well, the biologists get furious\nwith me for saying that,"},{"time":122504,"text":"because we have absolutely no evidence\nfor life beyond Earth yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126977,"text":"Well, if we were able to look\nat our galaxy from the outside"},{"time":131794,"text":"and zoom in to where our sun is,"},{"time":134026,"text":"we see a real map of the stars."},{"time":136046,"text":"And the highlighted stars\nare those with known exoplanets."},{"time":139745,"text":"This is really just\nthe tip of the iceberg."},{"time":142642,"text":"Here, this animation is zooming in\nonto our solar system."},{"time":146872,"text":"And you'll see here the planets"},{"time":148381,"text":"as well as some spacecraft\nthat are also orbiting our sun."},{"time":152968,"text":"Now if we can imagine going\nto the West Coast of North America,"},{"time":156356,"text":"and looking out at the night sky,"},{"time":158506,"text":"here's what we'd see on a spring night."},{"time":160808,"text":"And you can see\nthe constellations overlaid"},{"time":162842,"text":"and again, so many stars with planets."},{"time":165135,"text":"There's a special patch of the sky\nwhere we have thousands of planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169353,"text":"This is where the Kepler Space Telescope\nfocused for many years."},{"time":173576,"text":"Let's zoom in and look\nat one of the favorite exoplanets."},{"time":178863,"text":"This star is called Kepler-186f."},{"time":182529,"text":"It's a system of about five planets."},{"time":184751,"text":"And by the way, most of these exoplanets,\nwe don't know too much about."},{"time":188600,"text":"We know their size, and their orbit\nand things like that."},{"time":191607,"text":"But there's a very special planet\nhere called Kepler-186f."},{"time":195593,"text":"This planet is in a zone\nthat is not too far from the star,"},{"time":199721,"text":"so that the temperature\nmay be just right for life."},{"time":203004,"text":"Here, the artist's conception\nis just zooming in"},{"time":206059,"text":"and showing you what that planet\nmight be like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211074,"text":"So, many people have this\nromantic notion of astronomers"},{"time":216700,"text":"going to the telescope\non a lonely mountaintop"},{"time":220280,"text":"and looking at the spectacular night sky\nthrough a big telescope."},{"time":223853,"text":"But actually, we just work\non our computers like everyone else,"},{"time":227249,"text":"and we get our data by email\nor downloading from a database."},{"time":231098,"text":"So instead of coming here to tell you"},{"time":233645,"text":"about the somewhat tedious nature\nof the data and data analysis"},{"time":236800,"text":"and the complex computer models we make,"},{"time":238890,"text":"I have a different way\nto try to explain to you"},{"time":241112,"text":"some of the things\nthat we're thinking about exoplanets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243781,"text":"Here's a travel poster:"},{"time":244971,"text":"\"Kepler-186f:"},{"time":247315,"text":"Where the grass is always redder\non the other side.\""},{"time":250053,"text":"That's because Kepler-186f\norbits a red star,"},{"time":253807,"text":"and we're just speculating\nthat perhaps the plants there,"},{"time":256523,"text":"if there is vegetation\nthat does photosynthesis,"},{"time":259165,"text":"it has different pigments and looks red."},{"time":262137,"text":"\"Enjoy the gravity on HD 40307g,"},{"time":266519,"text":"a Super-Earth.\""},{"time":268002,"text":"This planet is more massive than Earth"},{"time":270183,"text":"and has a higher surface gravity."},{"time":272333,"text":"\"Relax on Kepler-16b,"},{"time":275254,"text":"where your shadow always has company.\""},{"time":277174,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":279158,"text":"We know of a dozen planets\nthat orbit two stars,"},{"time":283364,"text":"and there's likely many more out there."},{"time":285507,"text":"If we could visit one of those planets,"},{"time":287492,"text":"you literally would see two sunsets"},{"time":289403,"text":"and have two shadows."},{"time":291484,"text":"So actually, science fiction\ngot some things right."},{"time":293925,"text":"Tatooine from Star Wars."},{"time":296047,"text":"And I have a couple of other\nfavorite exoplanets"},{"time":298366,"text":"to tell you about."},{"time":299587,"text":"This one is Kepler-10b,"},{"time":301143,"text":"it's a hot, hot planet."},{"time":303642,"text":"It orbits over 50 times closer to its star"},{"time":306601,"text":"than our Earth does to our sun."},{"time":308792,"text":"And actually, it's so hot,"},{"time":310396,"text":"we can't visit any\nof these planets, but if we could,"},{"time":313053,"text":"we would melt long before we got there."},{"time":315051,"text":"We think the surface\nis hot enough to melt rock"},{"time":317404,"text":"and has liquid lava lakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319457,"text":"Gliese 1214b."},{"time":321065,"text":"This planet, we know the mass and the size"},{"time":323188,"text":"and it has a fairly low density."},{"time":324800,"text":"It's somewhat warm."},{"time":326053,"text":"We actually don't know\nreally anything about this planet,"},{"time":328761,"text":"but one possibility\nis that it's a water world,"},{"time":331290,"text":"like a scaled-up version\nof one of Jupiter's icy moons"},{"time":334821,"text":"that might be 50 percent water by mass."},{"time":337328,"text":"And in this case, it would have\na thick steam atmosphere"},{"time":340313,"text":"overlaying an ocean,"},{"time":342193,"text":"not of liquid water,"},{"time":343727,"text":"but of an exotic form\nof water, a superfluid --"},{"time":346756,"text":"not quite a gas, not quite a liquid."},{"time":348770,"text":"And under that wouldn't be rock,"},{"time":350394,"text":"but a form of high-pressure ice,"},{"time":352014,"text":"like ice IX."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354593,"text":"So out of all these planets out there,"},{"time":356792,"text":"and the variety\nis just simply astonishing,"},{"time":360030,"text":"we mostly want to find the planets\nthat are Goldilocks planets, we call them."},{"time":365184,"text":"Not too big, not too small,"},{"time":367125,"text":"not too hot, not too cold --"},{"time":368996,"text":"but just right for life."},{"time":370658,"text":"But to do that,\nwe'd have to be able to look"},{"time":372800,"text":"at the planet's atmosphere,"},{"time":374158,"text":"because the atmosphere\nacts like a blanket trapping heat --"},{"time":376978,"text":"the greenhouse effect."},{"time":378338,"text":"We have to be able to assess\nthe greenhouse gases"},{"time":381182,"text":"on other planets."},{"time":383169,"text":"Well, science fiction\ngot some things wrong."},{"time":385796,"text":"The Star Trek Enterprise"},{"time":387210,"text":"had to travel vast distances\nat incredible speeds"},{"time":390861,"text":"to orbit other planets"},{"time":392614,"text":"so that First Officer Spock\ncould analyze the atmosphere"},{"time":396614,"text":"to see if the planet was habitable"},{"time":398599,"text":"or if there were lifeforms there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400745,"text":"Well, we don't need\nto travel at warp speeds"},{"time":403259,"text":"to see other planet atmospheres,"},{"time":405412,"text":"although I don't want to dissuade\nany budding engineers"},{"time":408220,"text":"from figuring out how to do that."},{"time":410167,"text":"We actually can and do study\nplanet atmospheres"},{"time":412483,"text":"from here, from Earth orbit."},{"time":414120,"text":"This is a picture, a photograph\nof the Hubble Space Telescope"},{"time":417321,"text":"taken by the shuttle Atlantis\nas it was departing"},{"time":420095,"text":"after the last\nhuman space flight to Hubble."},{"time":422358,"text":"They installed a new camera, actually,"},{"time":424268,"text":"that we use for exoplanet atmospheres."},{"time":426437,"text":"And so far, we've been able to study\ndozens of exoplanet atmospheres,"},{"time":431366,"text":"about six of them in great detail."},{"time":433514,"text":"But those are not\nsmall planets like Earth."},{"time":435710,"text":"They're big, hot planets\nthat are easy to see."},{"time":438128,"text":"We're not ready,"},{"time":439390,"text":"we don't have the right technology yet\nto study small exoplanets."},{"time":444106,"text":"But nevertheless,"},{"time":445288,"text":"I wanted to try to explain to you\nhow we study exoplanet atmospheres."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449652,"text":"I want you to imagine,\nfor a moment, a rainbow."},{"time":452532,"text":"And if we could look\nat this rainbow closely,"},{"time":455302,"text":"we would see that some\ndark lines are missing."},{"time":459127,"text":"And here's our sun,"},{"time":460572,"text":"the white light of our sun split up,"},{"time":462363,"text":"not by raindrops, but by a spectrograph."},{"time":464673,"text":"And you can see\nall these dark, vertical lines."},{"time":467148,"text":"Some are very narrow, some are wide,"},{"time":468982,"text":"some are shaded at the edges."},{"time":470431,"text":"And this is actually how astronomers\nhave studied objects in the heavens,"},{"time":474059,"text":"literally, for over a century."},{"time":475578,"text":"So here, each different atom and molecule"},{"time":478028,"text":"has a special set of lines,"},{"time":479577,"text":"a fingerprint, if you will."},{"time":481157,"text":"And that's how we study\nexoplanet atmospheres."},{"time":483918,"text":"And I'll just never forget\nwhen I started working"},{"time":486302,"text":"on exoplanet atmospheres 20 years ago,"},{"time":488182,"text":"how many people told me,"},{"time":489391,"text":"\"This will never happen."},{"time":490624,"text":"We'll never be able to study them.\nWhy are you bothering?\""},{"time":493438,"text":"And that's why I'm pleased to tell you\nabout all the atmospheres studied now,"},{"time":497136,"text":"and this is really a field of its own."},{"time":499009,"text":"So when it comes to\nother planets, other Earths,"},{"time":501555,"text":"in the future when we can observe them,"},{"time":503656,"text":"what kind of gases\nwould we be looking for?"},{"time":506144,"text":"Well, you know, our own Earth\nhas oxygen in the atmosphere"},{"time":509343,"text":"to 20 percent by volume."},{"time":511445,"text":"That's a lot of oxygen."},{"time":513457,"text":"But without plants\nand photosynthetic life,"},{"time":516226,"text":"there would be no oxygen,"},{"time":517660,"text":"virtually no oxygen in our atmosphere."},{"time":520116,"text":"So oxygen is here because of life."},{"time":522063,"text":"And our goal then is to look for gases\nin other planet atmospheres,"},{"time":526194,"text":"gases that don't belong,"},{"time":528255,"text":"that we might be able\nto attribute to life."},{"time":530662,"text":"But which molecules should we search for?"},{"time":532767,"text":"I actually told you\nhow diverse exoplanets are."},{"time":535454,"text":"We expect that to continue in the future"},{"time":537475,"text":"when we find other Earths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538800,"text":"And that's one of the main things\nI'm working on now,"},{"time":541396,"text":"I have a theory about this."},{"time":542713,"text":"It reminds me that nearly every day,"},{"time":545025,"text":"I receive an email or emails"},{"time":547701,"text":"from someone with a crazy theory\nabout physics of gravity"},{"time":551352,"text":"or cosmology or some such."},{"time":553208,"text":"So, please don't email me\none of your crazy theories."},{"time":556565,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":557803,"text":"Well, I had my own crazy theory."},{"time":560005,"text":"But, who does the MIT professor go to?"},{"time":562703,"text":"Well, I emailed a Nobel Laureate\nin Physiology or Medicine"},{"time":566938,"text":"and he said, \"Sure, come and talk to me.\""},{"time":568935,"text":"So I brought my two biochemistry friends"},{"time":570958,"text":"and we went to talk to him\nabout our crazy theory."},{"time":573334,"text":"And that theory was that life\nproduces all small molecules,"},{"time":576799,"text":"so many molecules."},{"time":578497,"text":"Like, everything I could think of,\nbut not being a chemist."},{"time":581416,"text":"Think about it:"},{"time":582623,"text":"carbon dioxide, carbon monoxide,"},{"time":584677,"text":"molecular hydrogen, molecular nitrogen,"},{"time":586560,"text":"methane, methyl chloride --"},{"time":587950,"text":"so many gases."},{"time":589135,"text":"They also exist for other reasons,"},{"time":591094,"text":"but just life even produces ozone."},{"time":592970,"text":"So we go to talk to him about this,"},{"time":594752,"text":"and immediately, he shot down the theory."},{"time":597226,"text":"He found an example that didn't exist."},{"time":599948,"text":"So, we went back to the drawing board"},{"time":601753,"text":"and we think we have found something\nvery interesting in another field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605205,"text":"But back to exoplanets,"},{"time":606649,"text":"the point is that life produces\nso many different types of gases,"},{"time":609952,"text":"literally thousands of gases."},{"time":612188,"text":"And so what we're doing now\nis just trying to figure out"},{"time":614879,"text":"on which types of exoplanets,"},{"time":616492,"text":"which gases could be attributed to life."},{"time":622182,"text":"And so when it comes time\nwhen we find gases"},{"time":624254,"text":"in exoplanet atmospheres"},{"time":625629,"text":"that we won't know\nif they're being produced"},{"time":627749,"text":"by intelligent aliens or by trees,"},{"time":630803,"text":"or a swamp,"},{"time":632037,"text":"or even just by simple,\nsingle-celled microbial life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635541,"text":"So working on the models"},{"time":637115,"text":"and thinking about biochemistry,"},{"time":638790,"text":"it's all well and good."},{"time":640011,"text":"But a really big challenge\nahead of us is: how?"},{"time":642920,"text":"How are we going to find these planets?"},{"time":645106,"text":"There are actually many ways\nto find planets,"},{"time":647310,"text":"several different ways."},{"time":648853,"text":"But the one that I'm most focused on\nis how can we open a gateway"},{"time":652736,"text":"so that in the future,"},{"time":653997,"text":"we can find hundreds of Earths."},{"time":655870,"text":"We have a real shot\nat finding signs of life."},{"time":658227,"text":"And actually, I just finished\nleading a two-year project"},{"time":661377,"text":"in this very special phase"},{"time":663489,"text":"of a concept we call the starshade."},{"time":666167,"text":"And the starshade\nis a very specially shaped screen"},{"time":669144,"text":"and the goal is to fly that starshade"},{"time":671035,"text":"so it blocks out the light of a star"},{"time":674153,"text":"so that the telescope\ncan see the planets directly."},{"time":677116,"text":"Here, you can see myself\nand two team members"},{"time":679533,"text":"holding up one small part\nof the starshade."},{"time":681746,"text":"It's shaped like a giant flower,"},{"time":683350,"text":"and this is one of the prototype petals."},{"time":686907,"text":"The concept is that a starshade\nand telescope could launch together,"},{"time":691392,"text":"with the petals unfurling\nfrom the stowed position."},{"time":694896,"text":"The central truss would expand,"},{"time":696976,"text":"with the petals snapping into place."},{"time":700092,"text":"Now, this has to be made very precisely,"},{"time":702346,"text":"literally, the petals to microns"},{"time":703958,"text":"and they have to deploy to millimeters."},{"time":706697,"text":"And this whole structure would have to fly"},{"time":708776,"text":"tens of thousands of kilometers\naway from the telescope."},{"time":712159,"text":"It's about tens of meters in diameter."},{"time":714785,"text":"And the goal is to block out\nthe starlight to incredible precision"},{"time":719762,"text":"so that we'd be able to see\nthe planets directly."},{"time":723333,"text":"And it has to be a very special shape,"},{"time":725586,"text":"because of the physics of defraction."},{"time":727499,"text":"Now this is a real project\nthat we worked on,"},{"time":729742,"text":"literally, you would not believe how hard."},{"time":732234,"text":"Just so you believe\nit's not just in movie format,"},{"time":734920,"text":"here's a real photograph"},{"time":736580,"text":"of a second-generation\nstarshade deployment test bed in the lab."},{"time":741595,"text":"And in this case,\nI just wanted you to know"},{"time":743698,"text":"that that central truss\nhas heritage left over"},{"time":746212,"text":"from large radio deployables in space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749372,"text":"So after all of that hard work"},{"time":751052,"text":"where we try to think of all the crazy\ngases that might be out there,"},{"time":754869,"text":"and we build the very\ncomplicated space telescopes"},{"time":757821,"text":"that might be out there,"},{"time":759072,"text":"what are we going to find?"},{"time":760725,"text":"Well, in the best case,"},{"time":762507,"text":"we will find an image\nof another exo-Earth."},{"time":766328,"text":"Here is Earth as a pale blue dot."},{"time":768611,"text":"And this is actually\na real photograph of Earth"},{"time":771194,"text":"taken by the Voyager 1 spacecraft,"},{"time":773088,"text":"four billion miles away."},{"time":775159,"text":"And that red light is just scattered light\nin the camera optics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779315,"text":"But what's so awesome to consider"},{"time":781735,"text":"is that if there are intelligent aliens"},{"time":784808,"text":"orbiting on a planet\naround a star near to us"},{"time":788786,"text":"and they build complicated\nspace telescopes"},{"time":790855,"text":"of the kind that we're trying to build,"},{"time":792806,"text":"all they'll see is this pale blue dot,"},{"time":795330,"text":"a pinprick of light."},{"time":797456,"text":"And so sometimes, when I pause to think"},{"time":800546,"text":"about my professional struggle\nand huge ambition,"},{"time":804823,"text":"it's hard to think about that"},{"time":806840,"text":"in contrast to the vastness\nof the universe."},{"time":810120,"text":"But nonetheless, I am devoting\nthe rest of my life"},{"time":814270,"text":"to finding another Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816296,"text":"And I can guarantee"}]},{"cues":[{"time":818535,"text":"that in the next generation\nof space telescopes,"},{"time":820942,"text":"in the second generation,"},{"time":822506,"text":"we will have the capability\nto find and identity other Earths."},{"time":827936,"text":"And the capability\nto split up the starlight"},{"time":830634,"text":"so that we can look for gases"},{"time":832211,"text":"and assess the greenhouse gases\nin the atmosphere,"},{"time":835721,"text":"estimate the surface temperature,"},{"time":837343,"text":"and look for signs of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839736,"text":"But there's more."},{"time":841181,"text":"In this case of searching\nfor other planets like Earth,"},{"time":844569,"text":"we are making a new kind of map"},{"time":847188,"text":"of the nearby stars\nand of the planets orbiting them,"},{"time":850472,"text":"including [planets] that actually might be\ninhabitable by humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854915,"text":"And so I envision that our descendants,"},{"time":857320,"text":"hundreds of years from now,"},{"time":859149,"text":"will embark on an interstellar\njourney to other worlds."},{"time":863059,"text":"And they will look back at all of us"},{"time":865995,"text":"as the generation who first found\nthe Earth-like worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869822,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870997,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":877532,"text":"June Cohen: And I give you,\nfor a question,"},{"time":879656,"text":"Rosetta Mission Manager Fred Jansen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881817,"text":"Fred Jansen: You mentioned halfway through"},{"time":883872,"text":"that the technology\nto actually look at the spectrum"},{"time":887683,"text":"of an exoplanet like Earth\nis not there yet."},{"time":890336,"text":"When do you expect this will be there,"},{"time":892247,"text":"and what's needed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":893539,"text":"Actually, what we expect is what we call\nour next-generation Hubble telescope."},{"time":898531,"text":"And this is called the James Webb\nSpace Telescope,"},{"time":900896,"text":"and that will launch in 2018,"},{"time":902623,"text":"and that's what we're going to do,"},{"time":904469,"text":"we're going to look\nat a special kind of planet"},{"time":906757,"text":"called transient exoplanets,"},{"time":908237,"text":"and that will be our first shot\nat studying small planets"},{"time":911362,"text":"for gases that might indicate\nthe planet is habitable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915477,"text":"JC: I'm going to ask you\none follow-up question, too, Sara,"},{"time":918310,"text":"as the generalist."},{"time":919540,"text":"So I am really struck\nby the notion in your career"},{"time":922657,"text":"of the opposition you faced,"},{"time":924080,"text":"that when you began thinking\nabout exoplanets,"},{"time":926248,"text":"there was extreme skepticism\nin the scientific community"},{"time":928938,"text":"that they existed,"},{"time":930113,"text":"and you proved them wrong."},{"time":931406,"text":"What did it take to take that on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":933143,"text":"SS: Well, the thing is that as scientists,"},{"time":935237,"text":"we're supposed to be skeptical,"},{"time":937219,"text":"because our job to make sure\nthat what the other person is saying"},{"time":940291,"text":"actually makes sense or not."},{"time":941654,"text":"But being a scientist,"},{"time":944235,"text":"I think you've seen it from this session,"},{"time":946679,"text":"it's like being an explorer."},{"time":948385,"text":"You have this immense curiosity,"},{"time":950398,"text":"this stubbornness,"},{"time":951721,"text":"this sort of resolute will\nthat you will go forward"},{"time":954127,"text":"no matter what other people say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":956182,"text":"JC: I love that. Thank you, Sara."}]},{"cues":[{"time":957882,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}